learned to use them with some sort of reverence. I won't say I'm sorry
for something until I am genuinely sorry even if it is blatantly
obvious right then and there that I am wrong. I can't bring myself to
say something like that, and not mean it. I would rather have time to
think about the offense that was taken by someone else, than to just
say the words and not mean it. I don't know about you guys (and gals)
but that's just the way I operate......or at least try to.

